  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get your largest high-sided frying pan or casserole over a high heat. Drizzle in a good glug of olive oil. Season the chicken pieces generously with salt and black pepper then place skin-side down into the pan. Fry for 5–6 mins, turning occasionally, until the skin is evenly golden. You may need to do this in two batches."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, thinly slice the onions, peppers and garlic. Once the chicken is nicely browned, set aside on a plate. Reduce the heat to medium and scrape the onions and peppers into the pan. Add a pinch of salt then fry, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes until soft."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Scrape in the garlic, cook for 1 minute more then add the chilli flakes and rosemary. Stir together then spoon in the tomato purée. Give everything a good mix then pour in the red wine. Leave to bubble away until reduced by half, then tip in the tins of plum tomatoes. Bring thesauce to the boil."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drain the beans and add to the pan along with the olives. Season well with salt and black pepper then nestle the chicken pieces in. Put on a lid and leave to simmer away for 20 minutes. Remove the lid and cook for a further 10 mins until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has reduced slightly. Season with salt, black pepper and a splash of balsamic vinegar."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Roughly chop the parsley and scatter over the top. Serve at the table for people to help themselves. We like to eat this with a crusty ciabatta."
    }
  ],
